The CXO Magazine

Leading with Impact: The New DNA of the Modern CXO

Featuring Indra Nooyi, Elon Musk, and Arundhati Bhattacharya sharing their playbooks for

responsible growth and resilient Leadership.

The CXO Magazine

  • Elon Musk

    CEO, SpaceX & Tesla

    Beyond Earth: SpaceXs Next Leap and Teslas Path Forward.


    Covers his dual challenge of pushing space commercialization while scaling sustainable energy on Earth. Looks at how he manages multiple C-suite roles and controversies.

  • Mary Barra

    CEO, General Motors

    Electrifying the Future: GMs Roadmap for Sustainable Mobility.


    Highlights include GMs investments in battery tech, plans for net zero by 2040, and how ESG measures are integrated into board decisions.

  • Arundhati B.

    Chairperson / Director

    Banking on Purpose: Governing Indias Financial Future.


    Discussion on regulation, fintech disruption, and how corporate governance is evolving in Indian

    banking.

  • Indra Nooyi

    CEO / Board Member, PepsiCo

    Boardroom Wisdom: From Growth to Giving Back.


    Focus on her mentorship programs, advice to young leaders, and her current work on food security and global nutrition challenges.

  • Satya Nadella

    CEO, Microsoft

    Leading in the AI Age: Ethics, Opportunity, and Scale.


    Interview focuses on how Nadella sees responsibilities around generative AI deployment, AI governance, and how Microsoft is balancing innovation with accountability.
